Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
disconnectDanglingPort(25.10)                    disconnectDanglingPort(25.10)

Name
       disconnectDanglingPort  -  Disconnects  dangling nets from ports in the
       whole design, from the top level to the bottom level

Syntax
       disconnectDanglingPort

       [-help]

       [-keepInput]

       [-keepOutput]

       [-keepInout]

       [-partitionOnly]

       Disconnects dangling nets from ports in the whole design, from the  top
       level  to  the  bottom level. Use reportDanglingPort to report the dan-
       gling ports.

       You can use the disconnectDanglingPort command after  importing  a  de-
       sign.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each disconnectDanglingPort parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man disconnectDanglingPort.

       -keepInput
              Keeps the input dangling port connected.

       -keepOutput
              Keeps the output dangling port connected.

       -keepInout
              Keeps the inout dangling port connected.

       -partitionOnly
              Disconnects dangling nets in partitions only.

              Default: Disconnects all dangling nets.

Examples
              * The following command disconnects dangling wires in partitions
                only:

                disconnectDanglingPort -partitionOnly

              * The following set of commands first reports the dangling ports
                and then disconnects them:

                innovus > reportDanglingPort -outfile danglingport.rpt

                Sample content of the file danglingport.rpt:

                Port sel of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0

                Port a of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0

                Port b of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0

                Port y of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0

                innovus > disconnectDanglingPort

                Port sel of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0 is disconnected...

                Port a of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0 is disconnected...

                Port b of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0 is disconnected...

                Port y of module user_DFT_inst_BandA_0 is disconnected...

                4 connected dangling ports are disconnected.

Related Information
              * deleteDanglingPort

              * reportDanglingPort

